WEBVTT

00:08.091 --> 00:09.297
[SCREAMING]

00:09.468 --> 00:10.628
[JASON SCREAMING]

00:11.762 --> 00:13.127
SooMe.

00:13.972 --> 00:15.428
-Back off.
-Keep out of this.

00:15.599 --> 00:18.136
-I don't take orders from vamps.
-Get away from her.

00:18.310 --> 00:21.973
-Tara, he saved her life.
-After he almost fucking killed her.

00:22.147 --> 00:24.604
-You're alive. Sweet Jesus.
WOMAN: Is everything okay there?

00:24.775 --> 00:27.312
MAN: Yeah, she had a nightmare.
JASON: Sook?

00:27.486 --> 00:31.229
Say something. You brain damaged?

00:33.367 --> 00:37.531
|-- I need to speak to Bill, alone.

00:37.704 --> 00:40.446
So he can finish what he started?
Hell, no.

00:40.624 --> 00:41.989
Tara.

00:42.459 --> 00:46.748
-Everyone, please.
-Y'all heard her. Out.

01:04.314 --> 01:06.145
You're afraid of me.

01:07.359 --> 01:08.724
Can you blame me?

01:09.945 --> 01:11.901
I never meant to hurt you.

01:15.867 --> 01:18.700
-I couldn't stop.
-I know.

01:18.870 --> 01:21.657
I can't take back what I've done.

01:22.332 --> 01:25.369
No, you can't.

01:26.378 --> 01:29.245
I don't know how to start forgiving you.

01:29.423 --> 01:33.336
Don't know if I ever will.
There's too much.

01:33.510 --> 01:36.001
I'm not asking for your forgiveness.

01:37.848 --> 01:39.509
I don't wanna be forgiven.

01:39.683 --> 01:46.600
From the day we met,
it's been one long, bloody fight.

01:48.191 --> 01:51.524
And I keep waiting for it to be over...

01:52.613 --> 01:54.444
...for us to be happy...

01:55.490 --> 02:00.610
...to start our lives together
like a normal couple.

02:03.373 --> 02:08.037
-But it's never gonna happen for us, is it?
-I want you to have all that.

02:09.379 --> 02:12.246
I want you to lie in the sunlight...

02:13.634 --> 02:15.590
...have children...

02:17.054 --> 02:18.760
...grow old with someone.

02:18.930 --> 02:21.307
I want you to have the life you deserve.

02:24.811 --> 02:27.063
And I cannot give it to you.

02:29.941 --> 02:31.272
[CRYING]

02:33.111 --> 02:35.898
I love you, Sookie Stackhouse...

02:36.740 --> 02:38.605
...and I will love you forever.

02:40.869 --> 02:42.825
I love you too.

02:53.382 --> 02:55.088
Be safe.

03:02.432 --> 03:04.423
[SOBBING]

04:57.172 --> 04:58.537
[BIRD SQUAWKING]

04:58.715 --> 05:02.082
SOPHIE ANNE:
This isn't a room, it's a fucking closet.

05:03.804 --> 05:06.420
Where am I supposed to put my birds?
Hadley!

05:06.598 --> 05:08.680
You never said
she was going to live with us.

05:08.850 --> 05:10.306
She's my wife, Talbot.

05:10.477 --> 05:14.220
We just acquired the state of Louisiana.
I thought you would've been excited.

05:14.397 --> 05:15.978
Excited?

05:16.149 --> 05:18.561
Franklin's brains won't wash off
the guest linens...

05:18.735 --> 05:21.226
...I had to bury werewolves
under the gazebo...

05:21.404 --> 05:24.111
...and that Sookie bitch staked Lorena.

05:24.282 --> 05:26.193
I've had enough excitement, thank you.

05:26.409 --> 05:27.694
[TALBOT SPEAKING IN GREEK]

05:30.247 --> 05:32.659
RUSSELL:
They made quite a mess, didn't they?

05:34.918 --> 05:36.249
Well, at least you're safe.

05:37.420 --> 05:39.251
That's what matters most to me.

05:40.382 --> 05:41.417
Words.

05:44.678 --> 05:47.545
Oh, things may be
getting complicated soon.

05:47.722 --> 05:51.556
I'm afraid I acted somewhat impulsively
while I was gone.

05:51.726 --> 05:53.762
What did you do?

05:53.937 --> 05:56.269
-Spit it out.
-I killed the Magister.

05:57.816 --> 05:59.898
He deserved it.

06:00.068 --> 06:01.274
Are you out of your mind?

06:01.444 --> 06:04.277
-The Authority will never stand for it--
-Fuck the Authority.

06:04.447 --> 06:07.280
They won't be able to prove a thing.
I made sure of that.

06:07.450 --> 06:10.817
-You're acting like a century-old child.
-Relax!

06:11.413 --> 06:15.782
I've sent a check to the AVL in support
of their foolish Vampire Rights Amendment.

06:15.959 --> 06:20.168
-You can't buy your way out of everything.
-Of course I can. This is America.

06:20.338 --> 06:22.954
Forgive the interruption, Your Majesty.

06:24.134 --> 06:27.171
There's a were-bitch in your study.

06:28.221 --> 06:31.884
Go, while I babysit your wife.

06:33.435 --> 06:34.470
[BIRD SQUAWKING]

06:34.644 --> 06:36.635
[TALBOT MUTTERING IN GREEK]

06:39.774 --> 06:42.561
RUSSELL: What's up, pumpkin?
-They killed my Cooter.

06:42.777 --> 06:45.154
Aw. He died a hero.

06:45.322 --> 06:47.153
He weren't no hero.

06:47.324 --> 06:50.316
He just wanted to do some V
and have a little fun.

06:50.493 --> 06:53.405
And they shot him in the heart.

06:54.748 --> 06:58.240
Let me go after them.
I'll rip their fucking heads off.

06:58.460 --> 06:59.495
[LAUGHS]

06:59.669 --> 07:02.502
I like your energy.
What do you think, Northman?

07:02.672 --> 07:06.210
Well, I enjoy a good head-ripping
as much as the next vampire...

07:07.177 --> 07:11.090
...but in this case, it might be wise to
consider the value of the heads in question.

07:11.264 --> 07:15.598
You mean the Stackhouse girl?
Yeah, she's something special, isn't she?

07:15.769 --> 07:18.431
She fucked my ex-boyfriend
and made him shoot my fiance.

07:18.605 --> 07:21.392
-She's a cunt.
-But she's a special cunt.

07:22.359 --> 07:26.398
Ah, don't worry, darling.
I'll let you play with her first.

07:28.239 --> 07:29.649
Go.

07:35.914 --> 07:40.704
Respectfully, Your Majesty,
given the recent turn of events...

07:40.877 --> 07:43.619
...bringing Sookie into this
may not be the best idea.

07:43.797 --> 07:47.381
Well, that's exactly why I need her.
I may have inadvertently started a war.

07:47.550 --> 07:49.757
Miss Stackhouse
could be my secret weapon.

07:49.928 --> 07:52.715
Well, Sookie's abilities
are unpredictable at best.

07:52.889 --> 07:55.551
And like most humans,
she's ruled by petty emotions.

07:55.725 --> 07:57.636
I would not trust her.

07:58.395 --> 08:01.478
The real question is: Can I trust you?

08:01.648 --> 08:03.559
You turned on your own queen.

08:03.733 --> 08:05.564
Now that I've freed your feisty ward...

08:05.735 --> 08:08.602
...how do I know
you won't sell me out as well?

08:13.076 --> 08:17.115
Because I have been searching for you
for a thousand years.

08:20.417 --> 08:21.998
A true leader.

08:23.003 --> 08:26.495
One strong enough to unite us all.

08:27.132 --> 08:33.469
I believed my maker, Godric,
was such a vampire, but he was weak.

08:33.638 --> 08:36.755
He succumbed to his humanity,
and it killed him.

08:37.767 --> 08:39.052
Dispatching the Magister...

08:39.227 --> 08:42.685
...that proved without a doubt
that my search...

08:43.481 --> 08:44.641
...it has finally ended.

08:44.816 --> 08:49.355
-That was rash and foolish.
-It was brave and uncompromising.

08:50.989 --> 08:53.196
Vampires have yearned
for someone to stand up...

08:53.366 --> 08:56.699
...to the tyranny of the Authority
for centuries.

09:01.124 --> 09:02.455
Just give me the chance...

09:08.548 --> 09:10.709
...and I will show you...

09:11.885 --> 09:15.127
...just how deep my loyalty runs.

09:20.060 --> 09:22.051
[TERRY SINGING "HUSH, LITTLE BABY"]

09:35.533 --> 09:36.784
ARLENE:
Hmph.

09:36.951 --> 09:39.203
When's Papa gonna buy Mama
a diamond ring?

09:41.081 --> 09:42.366
That's what I wanna know.

09:45.794 --> 09:47.785
[CONTINUES SINGING]

10:01.017 --> 10:02.348
[GASPS]

10:02.685 --> 10:04.346
Rene.

10:05.355 --> 10:07.346
Don't you worry, chere.

10:07.524 --> 10:10.436
I'll take real good care of our baby.

10:10.610 --> 10:12.896
Oh, no, you're dead.

10:13.863 --> 10:15.023
They buried you.

10:15.824 --> 10:18.190
Death can't keep me from my boy.

10:18.368 --> 10:20.450
You're gonna finish
what your daddy started...

10:20.620 --> 10:22.531
...ain't you, petit boug?

10:22.914 --> 10:25.280
Gonna be just like your old man, you.

10:25.458 --> 10:27.039
No.

10:27.210 --> 10:29.542
He ain't gonna be nothing like you.

10:29.712 --> 10:33.796
-You get away from us.
-l'm in his blood, boo.

10:34.509 --> 10:36.875
Ain't nothing you can do about that.

10:37.637 --> 10:39.377
[SCREAMING]

10:39.556 --> 10:42.218
Arlene! Wake up, wake up.

10:42.392 --> 10:44.223
[GASPING]

10:44.686 --> 10:45.801
You were dreaming, baby.

10:46.855 --> 10:48.846
[SOBBING]

10:50.900 --> 10:54.392
JESSICA: Oh, I never thought I'd miss you,
but I totally did.

10:55.363 --> 10:59.572
All right. There's some stuff I gotta tell you,
but you gotta promise you won't get mad.

10:59.742 --> 11:03.610
Jessica, there's no time for this.
Collect your things and leave immediately.

11:03.788 --> 11:05.904
-Where we going?
-We're not going anywhere.

11:06.082 --> 11:07.117
-But—-
-Look at me.

11:08.418 --> 11:11.000
As your maker, I release you.

11:12.380 --> 11:14.792
Well, what's that supposed to mean?

11:14.966 --> 11:18.174
It means our ties are broken.
You are free to go.

11:19.012 --> 11:21.719
Well, but what if
I don't wanna be released?

11:21.890 --> 11:25.178
-You can't stay with me.
-We|l, I ain't going anywhere. No way.

11:25.351 --> 11:27.262
-Listen to me.
-No, you listen to me.

11:28.188 --> 11:29.928
l drained someone.

11:31.274 --> 11:33.606
l was hungry and l was sad,
and it was an accident.

11:33.776 --> 11:36.438
I didn't know how to control myself.
You never taught me.

11:36.613 --> 11:38.774
No, I need you.
You are the only maker I've got.

11:38.948 --> 11:41.439
I can't take care of you!

11:41.618 --> 11:43.449
I can't protect you!

11:46.289 --> 11:48.450
I'm no good to you.

11:48.625 --> 11:50.741
Well, I'm no good either.

11:50.919 --> 11:54.832
And I don't care what you say,
I am not leaving.

11:58.968 --> 12:00.959
[CRYING]

12:03.932 --> 12:05.718
I don't wanna be alone anymore.

12:11.773 --> 12:13.764
[SOBBING]

12:42.303 --> 12:44.589
I don't wanna talk about it.

12:45.223 --> 12:46.929
Okay.

12:50.019 --> 12:53.932
If you need to get back to Jackson,
I understand.

12:54.107 --> 12:55.267
I'll be fine.

12:55.441 --> 12:58.558
Sookie, I know you're tougher
than a one-eared alley cat...

12:58.736 --> 13:00.727
...but I ain't leaving you alone right now.

13:02.573 --> 13:05.189
Besides, I reckon Jackson
won't be too friendly tonight.

13:05.368 --> 13:07.324
There's a guest room upstairs.

13:07.495 --> 13:09.531
You're welcome to it
for as long as you need.

13:14.210 --> 13:16.371
Someday it won't hurt so bad.

13:16.546 --> 13:19.538
Is that what you keep telling yourself
about Debbie?

13:20.133 --> 13:21.498
[DOOR OPENS]

13:23.136 --> 13:24.842
Andy, what are you doing here?

13:25.013 --> 13:28.221
Just because I let Bill give you his blood,
don't mean I forgive him.

13:28.391 --> 13:30.222
Sook, you need to press charges.

13:30.393 --> 13:34.136
What he did to you,
that's domestic...something.

13:34.314 --> 13:37.226
Actually, it sounds more like assault
or attempted murder.

13:37.400 --> 13:39.231
I'm not gonna press charges on Bill.

13:39.402 --> 13:41.563
Your brother's just trying
to look out for you.

13:41.738 --> 13:43.820
SOOKIE: I know, but Bill didn't attack me
on purpose.

13:44.240 --> 13:48.108
He was starving and unconscious.
It's his nature.

13:48.286 --> 13:49.992
That's no excuse.

13:53.833 --> 13:58.076
It's over between me and Bill.
There's nothing more to talk about.

13:58.254 --> 13:59.460
Maybe now is not the time.

13:59.630 --> 14:02.212
If you change your mind,
we can get a restraining order.

14:02.383 --> 14:04.590
No, screw the restraining order.

14:04.761 --> 14:07.673
If he come near you again,
I'm gonna kill him, I swear.

14:07.847 --> 14:09.178
You ain't killing nobody.

14:09.432 --> 14:11.969
[AS ON: Stop looking at me.
She's gonna hear what I 'm thinking.

14:12.143 --> 14:13.474
ANDY:
Don 't lose your shit on me.

14:13.644 --> 14:15.805
1A5 ON:
Fuck. Shut up, brain. She’s gonna find out.

14:15.980 --> 14:17.686
Jason. Find out what?

14:17.857 --> 14:20.849
-What have you done?
-Nothing.

14:21.027 --> 14:24.986
You got no right being in my head.
That's trespassing.

14:25.156 --> 14:26.191
I do so have a right.

14:26.366 --> 14:29.483
If you come into my house
threatening to kill people and lying.

14:29.660 --> 14:31.696
Fine. I'll leave.

14:32.080 --> 14:34.867
Somebody's gotta make that fanger pay
for what he did to you.

14:35.041 --> 14:39.125
That fanger?
Jason, that's not who you are.

14:39.295 --> 14:42.833
That's now how Gran raised you.
You ain't a bigot or a murderer.

14:43.299 --> 14:46.041
I know you love me
and you're just trying to protect me...

14:46.219 --> 14:48.551
...but I have seen enough killing
and hating.

14:48.721 --> 14:50.803
I can't take any more.

14:50.973 --> 14:52.383
Jason.

14:52.558 --> 14:55.971
Please just tell me
you ain't gonna do anything stupid.

14:56.813 --> 14:59.805
[EILEN JEWEL'S "TILL YOU LAY DOWN YOUR
HEAVY LOAD" PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

15:08.866 --> 15:10.857
You ever gonna tell me
what happened to you?

15:17.333 --> 15:19.073
Someday.

15:19.627 --> 15:21.743
Just not tonight.

15:22.839 --> 15:26.832
Well, hooker, I need to know.
You got a death wish?

15:28.177 --> 15:29.838
No.

15:30.346 --> 15:32.086
I don't.

15:33.099 --> 15:36.512
I fought like a motherfucker to survive.

15:38.563 --> 15:42.681
Never realized how much
I wanted to live till....

15:47.572 --> 15:50.689
I can't go there right now, Lafayette.

15:52.994 --> 15:54.655
Okay.

15:55.788 --> 15:58.200
You ain't got to go nowhere.

15:58.875 --> 16:01.491
You just stay right here with me.

16:11.471 --> 16:13.462
[SNIFFING]

16:22.148 --> 16:24.139
[WHIMPERING]

16:31.824 --> 16:34.736
Get in here before someone sees you.

16:38.331 --> 16:39.662
SAM:
Make sure that's everything.

16:40.458 --> 16:43.074
Because you ain't welcome back here,
you understand?

16:43.252 --> 16:47.916
I want you boys to know I don't blame you.
I'd leave us too if I could.

16:48.090 --> 16:49.466
What's stopping you?

16:49.634 --> 16:53.593
That son of a bitch done nothing
but knock you up and suck you dry.

16:53.763 --> 16:57.756
That son of a bitch is your daddy.
And he's my husband.

17:00.436 --> 17:02.427
I know he's no good...

17:02.605 --> 17:04.596
...but love don't discriminate.

17:04.774 --> 17:06.389
That's why--

17:08.194 --> 17:10.435
You can hate me if you want...

17:11.030 --> 17:13.112
...but I'll still love you.

17:14.242 --> 17:15.948
Both of y'all.

17:18.287 --> 17:20.744
As long as I'm still breathing.

17:25.002 --> 17:26.788
Tommy.

17:32.301 --> 17:34.633
Take care of my boy, Sam.

17:35.555 --> 17:37.887
Take care of yourself too.

17:41.811 --> 17:43.847
Let me help you with that.

17:44.021 --> 17:47.388
-l'm strongerthan I look.
-lbeHeveiL

17:47.900 --> 17:49.856
But if you wanna help...

17:50.152 --> 17:51.688
...I could really use some money.

17:53.823 --> 17:55.313
I know I got no right to ask...

17:55.491 --> 17:58.733
...but Joe Lee done spent
every cent we had on that fight.

18:01.622 --> 18:02.953
[SIGHS]

18:11.424 --> 18:13.005
That ain't gonna get us far.

18:13.175 --> 18:16.759
I don't give a fuck where it gets you
as long as it's out of here.

18:38.993 --> 18:40.984
[SOBBING]

18:47.835 --> 18:49.826
[SHOWER RUNNING]

19:11.901 --> 19:13.892
[MOANING]

19:19.116 --> 19:20.276
[SCREAMS]

19:30.961 --> 19:32.292
[GASPS]

19:33.756 --> 19:35.747
[PANTING]

19:49.230 --> 19:50.936
Motherfuck.

19:53.192 --> 19:58.027
-And now you can fly too. Ain't you fancy?
-Mama, how you get out the hospital?

19:58.197 --> 20:00.904
-And what are you doing here?
-Hell, I came to protect you.

20:01.075 --> 20:04.818
-They coming for you.
-Who? Who coming for me, Mama?

20:06.789 --> 20:10.498
The vampires, the witches...

20:11.585 --> 20:14.372
...the dogs and the cats, they know.

20:14.547 --> 20:17.209
They all know.

20:17.383 --> 20:19.044
And they are coming for you, baby.

20:19.218 --> 20:22.506
But I got here. I got here.

20:26.225 --> 20:27.556
[SOBS]

20:30.521 --> 20:33.012
TARA: Hey.
-Hi.

20:34.191 --> 20:36.273
TARA:
You wanna be alone?

20:44.535 --> 20:46.071
No.

20:47.997 --> 20:50.534
| used to do this all the time.

20:50.708 --> 20:54.997
Just lie in the sun
till the whole world faded away.

20:55.421 --> 20:58.709
And your Gran would yell
about you putting on sunscreen.

20:58.883 --> 21:02.751
BOTH:
"You're frying like a fritter in a pan."

21:04.305 --> 21:06.796
My whole life's at night now.

21:08.100 --> 21:10.591
You gonna go back to Bill again?

21:11.520 --> 21:13.932
No one's ever hurt me so bad.

21:14.565 --> 21:18.103
I trusted him with every part of me.

21:18.277 --> 21:21.189
Maybe it's stupid
to trust someone that much.

21:23.866 --> 21:25.572
You didn't ask for any of this.

21:25.743 --> 21:28.029
I knew what he was
the minute I laid eyes on him.

21:28.204 --> 21:29.614
I knew he was dangerous.

21:29.789 --> 21:32.781
And I ain't gonna lie,
that's part of what I fell in love with.

21:32.958 --> 21:35.074
Bill gave you his blood
before your first date.

21:35.252 --> 21:36.367
He saved my life.

21:36.545 --> 21:39.207
We both know what drinking their blood
does to you.

21:39.381 --> 21:41.542
He glamoured you
into thinking you were in love.

21:41.717 --> 21:43.753
Glamouring doesn't work on me.

21:43.928 --> 21:47.216
It might be over between me and Bill,
but what we had was real...

21:47.389 --> 21:50.722
...and l can'tjust flip a switch
and turn my heart off.

21:50.893 --> 21:52.884
You know what you sound like?

21:53.062 --> 21:54.927
One of those songs about dumb bitches...

21:55.105 --> 21:59.018
...who let their men cheat and beat on them,
all for the sake of true love.

21:59.193 --> 22:00.399
Let me tell you something.

22:00.569 --> 22:03.732
At the end of those songs,
the dumb bitches always end up dead.

22:03.906 --> 22:05.487
Did you just call me a dumb bitch?

22:05.658 --> 22:08.946
I'm sorry, but if you go back
to that vampire, that's what you are.

22:09.119 --> 22:13.738
What I can do in my brain,
it's every bit as deadly as Bill's fangs.

22:13.916 --> 22:16.328
I know what it's like
to be afraid of my own body...

22:16.502 --> 22:18.493
...to not be sure what it's gonna do next.

22:18.963 --> 22:20.294
I've killed.

22:20.464 --> 22:22.921
I may not have cheated, but I wanted to.

22:23.092 --> 22:25.799
-Me and Bill, we ain't so different.
-Yes, you are.

22:25.970 --> 22:27.756
I saw the look in his eye.

22:27.930 --> 22:32.674
Same as Franklin's: cold and crazy.

22:33.310 --> 22:36.347
-Like a rattlesnake.
-That isn't the Bill I know.

22:36.522 --> 22:42.108
-Then maybe you don't know the real Bill.
-Tara, I don't wanna fight with you.

22:42.278 --> 22:45.395
You've been through a lot.
I can see you're in pain.

22:45.573 --> 22:48.110
-Let's talk about it.
-I can't.

22:51.245 --> 22:54.783
Because trust me, Sook,
you don't wanna hear what I've gotta say.

22:54.957 --> 22:56.743
Morning, Tara.

23:00.796 --> 23:04.129
Good. Maybe you can flirt some sense
into that girl...

23:04.300 --> 23:07.292
...because logic sure as hell
ain't working.

23:29.658 --> 23:30.818
[POUNDING ON DOOR]

23:30.993 --> 23:32.779
Hold on.

23:32.953 --> 23:34.944
[POUNDING CONTINUES]

23:35.122 --> 23:37.238
Yeah, I'm coming.

